    <p class="sl">Appliance-side vs. Plumbing-side</p>
    <h2>What our prices cover — and what belongs to a plumber</h2>
    <p class="lead">Garbage disposal repair straddles two service categories in LA: appliance repair (motor, switch, reset, impeller, electrical) and plumbing (drain line, pipe connections, sewer backup). Our prices above are appliance-side only. Plumbing-side work is honestly out of our scope.</p>

    <div class="body-text">
      <p><strong>What our $89–$260 labor bands cover (appliance-side):</strong> jammed impeller + humming-not-spinning diagnostic + thermal overload reset + wall switch + GFCI circuit + motor replacement + worn seal (bottom / flange / dishwasher port) + impeller plate replacement + jam clearing + grinding chamber cleaning + descaling for LA hard-water mineral buildup.</p>
      <p><strong>What a plumber handles (out of our scope):</strong> drain line clogs downstream of the disposal + P-trap and drain pipe connections + sewer line backup + water supply lines + original drain rough-in work + complex sink-flange corrosion requiring drain reconfiguration.</p>
      <p>When we arrive and diagnose a plumbing-side issue, we'll tell you plainly before charging anything beyond the $89 diagnostic — and in most cases, if the issue is entirely plumbing-scope (water backing up from multiple drains, no disposal symptom at all), we'll let you know on the phone before we dispatch. Plumbing rates in LA run $150–$350/hour for most drain work vs. our $89–$260 labor range — different service, different cost structure.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block" style="margin-top: 24px;">
      <div class="tip-label">Scope boundary — quick reference</div>
      <p><strong>Call us (appliance):</strong> humming, jammed, won't start, reset keeps tripping, motor burned out, impeller broken, bottom-seal leak. <strong>Call a plumber (plumbing):</strong> water backing up from sinks that don't have a disposal, drain line fully clogged below disposal, sink drain slow on multiple fixtures.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

