    <p class="sl">Brand Routing</p>
    <h2>How brand badges affect pricing — or don't</h2>
    <p class="lead">Disposals in LA run a narrower brand field than most appliances. Most secondary-badge units are InSinkErator chassis underneath, which keeps parts availability strong and pricing consistent across brand labels.</p>

    <div class="body-text">
      <p>InSinkErator (Emerson Racine WI) and Waste King (Anaheim CA — LA-local) dominate LA installs. KitchenAid + Whirlpool + GE disposals are typically InSinkErator-OEM'd with different badges; our prices above apply the same way across these secondary brands because the internals are usually shared. Moen disposals (Fort Madison IA plumbing-fixture brand) use their own platform but parts are readily sourced through LA distributors — same pricing tier.</p>
      <p>Commercial/foodservice brands (Waste Maid + Salvajor + Red Lion) are NOT residential scope. If you have a commercial disposal in a restaurant or commercial-kitchen setting, different service category with different electrical + health-department coding — we don't service commercial disposals at this time.</p>
      <p>For the full brand context including HP sizing and continuous-feed vs. batch-feed architecture, see our <a href="/services/garbage-disposal-repair/">garbage disposal repair service page</a> with full brand-index and architecture detail.</p>
